comments: Caldwell-Pope (WAS) swipes downwards with his left arm and makes contact with the ball and then left arm of Wagner (ORL)  after the latter's gather during the driving shot attempt at the rim.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Harris (ORL) and marginal contact occurs as Harris switches the screen with Ross (ORL).
Beal (WAS) and Ross (ORL) briefly engage and disengage while in pursuit of the rebound and some marginal contact occurs.
Dinwiddie (WAS) places a marginal forearm on Wagner's (ORL) back and disengages without dislodging him from his position.  Gafford (WAS) and Wagner make incidental contact during the rebound.
Bamba (ORL) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Beal (WAS) and absorbs the contact from the defensive player.
Bamba (ORL) places a forearm to the back of Gafford (WAS) during the rebound but does not extend before removing it and going into the air to secure the offensive rebound.

As Kuzma (WAS) goes to set the pick on Ross (ORL), Wagner (ORL), who had two hands to Kuzma's side, extends his arms slightly but the contact is marginal and Kuzma is not rendered out of control when setting the screen.
Bamba (ORL) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Dinwiddie (WAS) and is firming up when he absorbs contact from Dinwiddie on the screen.

Replay review of the shooting foul called on Gafford (WAS) pursuant to a coach?s challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  	Gafford makes contact with Anthony's (ORL) arm and body that affects his shot attempt at the rim.
Anthony (ORL) makes contact to the arm of Beal (WAS) while attempting to make play for the ball but the contact is exceedingly brief and marginal. Beal's pass to Kuzma (WAS) is unaffected.
Harris (ORL) commits a take foul on Kuzma (WAS).
Anthony (ORL) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Dinwiddie (WAS) and provides Dinwiddie space to avoid the backscreen.
Okeke (ORL) commits a take foul on Beal (WAS).
Beal (WAS) legally contests Harris' (ORL) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Kuzma (WAS) touches the ball before it has reached its apex and is on its way down.
